  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIf you run `truffle console`, close it and open it again, the commands you used the first time won't be available in the REPL history.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run `truffle console`\r\n2. Write `1+1`\r\n3. Close the console\r\n4. Run `truffle console` again\r\n5. Press the up arrow\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`1+1` should appear\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nNothing happens (no history available)\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 17.04 x86_64\r\n* Truffle version: 3.4.11\r\n* Ethereum client: testrpc\r\n* node version: 8.7.0\r\n* npm version: 5.4.2\r\n",
