    "body": "I added some hacky code to my globally installed Truffle npm module to get this working. Just find wherever Truffle is installed (for me it was `~/.nvm/versions/node/v6.11.3/lib/node_modules/truffle`) and add the following code to your `truffle/build/cli.bundled.js`.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n    // Added this after `this.repl = repl.start...` in `ReplManager.prototype.start`.\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n      fs.statSync('.truffle_console_history');\r\n    } catch(e) {\r\n      fs.writeFileSync('.truffle_console_history', '');\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    fs.readFileSync('.truffle_console_history')\r\n      .toString()\r\n      .split('\\n')\r\n      .reverse()\r\n      .filter(line => line.trim())\r\n      .map(line => this.repl.history.push(line));\r\n\r\n    this.repl.on(\"line\", function(line) {\r\n      fs.appendFileSync('.truffle_console_history', line + '\\n');\r\n    });\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is incredibly brittle, and might or might not work depending on your Node/Truffle version. Would be nice to have this baked into Truffle's REPL.",
